She was 77. Her timing, wails and pratfalls had made the I Love Lucy show one of the most popular in television history. That legacy involved Miss Ball and her late former husband, Cuban band leader Desi Arnaz. The couple went on a nationwide vaudeville tour and proved that audiences would sit still to watch a leggy, blue-eyed comedian and a Cuban-born band leader with a heavy accent.  Paley, chairman of CBS Inc. In all, she appeared in more than 75 movies. They starred regularly from 1951 to 1957 as Lucy and Ricky Ricardo in I Love Lucy. 